trans-unit.source: View the cost shares of all items in the parent item's product structure, their quantity and their cost shares specified in material, capacity, overhead, and total cost. Material cost is calculated as the cost of all items in the parent item's product structure. Capacity and subcontractor costs are calculated as the costs related to produce all of the items in the parent item's product structure. Material cost is calculated as the cost of all items in the item's product structure. Capacity and subcontractor costs are the cost related to the parent item only.

Kapacitet og underleverandøromkostninger beregnes som omkostningerne i forbindelse med fremstilling af alle varerne i den overordnede vares produktstruktur. Materielle omkostninger beregnes som omkostningerne for alle varer i varens produktstruktur. Kapacitet og underleverandøromkostninger er kun omkostningerne relateret til den overordnede vare.

trans-unit.source: Specifies a description for the item costing setup

If a part of the production order has been produced (Finished quantity < Quantity): the system calculates the consumption of materials and the times to be costed as a ratio between the 2 quantities (as in the calculation of the true WIP). If, on the other hand, the production order has been completed (Finished quantity >= Quantity), regardless of the status of the order, the system only costs the materials and actual times recorded (it does not recalculate anything). This logic also determines the calculation of the final amounts and the final unit costs present in the routing history.
trans-unit.target: Hvis en PO er delvist produceret (færdig mængde <Mængde) beregner systemet forbruget af materialer og de tider, der skal beregnes som et forhold mellem de 2 mængder. Hvis PO'en derimod er færdigproduceret (Færdig mængde> = Antal), uanset status på selve PO'en, koster systemet kun de materialer og faktisk registrerede tider (det foretager ingen genberegning). Denne logik bestemmer også beregningen af ​​de endelige beløb og de endelige enhedsomkostninger, der er til stede i cyklushistorien.
